text:
Wait, <@UG81XCYBS> is from Spike Feeders? Dope.

Are you the player who played the Aetherlich deck?
Yep!

AWESOME.

That deck was amazing to watch in one of your videos. One of my favorite deck concepts ever.
It is the weirdest deck I have ever built by a pretty huge margin
Replacement effect city
I remember seeing a primer about it on the rEDH sub, and then it popping up in your videos. I’m a more conservative deck-builder, but one day I’ll try making that Lich effect a center-piece.

At one point, we talked about deck goals and discussed the difference between having a deck that is an engine vs. having a specific “goal” in a deck.

Not characterizing your deck or your style as such, but that type of mindset is rough for me.
Ah yeah
That deck was part of a series of centrepiece decks I built around cedh staples
I also built a derevi mill deck, a 65 land jund ad nauseam deck, and a riku protean hulk deck
They are fun, but nowhere close to Aetherlich
Do you have a deck you’d say is the one you enjoy playing the most?
Hmmm
I play a lot of anax & cymede
Just to rebel against all the people who dump on boros
<http://tappedout.net/mtg-decks/anax-aggro/>

attachments.title: MTG Deck: Anax Aggro
attachments.text: IntroductionThis is my favourite Boros deck of all time. It's fast and hits like...

text: I also really like playing Sygg 8 rack, but it isn't the type of casual deck I can play against strangers. On the competitive side I *love* Momir Vig hackball, and this dumb bears in cars list I have been noodling with
I didn’t know what to expect from that Anex and Cymede deck but seeing Akroan Crusader was enough. That’s awesome.
The general idea is that boros has access to enchantress effects for CA, and playing aura voltron on a&c lets you swing in for massive damage with weenies
Then the rest of the deck is stuff like [[mark of fury]] and rebound so you can get a little more than a card worth of advantage from casting each spell
